cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper discusses data augmentation techniques in deep learning, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of data augmentation on generalization error, which is a common topic in the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
